             The Swedish krona weakened against
the euro after the Riksbank said its repo rate wonâ€™t need to be
increased as much as previously assumed.  
 The krona fell 0.4 percent to 9.5687 per euro as of 9:34
a.m. in Stockholm.  
 The Swedish central bank also raised its main rate by a
quarter point to 0.50 percent, matching a median prediction by
economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  
